13594|date=11 May 1920|page=1240|city=e |nolink=y}}</ref>\n*Grand Cordon of the [[Order of the Rising Sun]] of the [[Empire of Japan]] \u2013 21 January 1921<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=32201 |supp=y|date=21 January 1921|page=572|nolink=y}}</ref>\n*Grand Cordon of the [[Order of the Paulownia Flowers]] of the [[Empire of Japan]] \u2013 20 January 1922<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=32586|date=24 January 1922|page=641|nolink=y}}</ref>\n*Grand Cross (Mil.) of the [[Order of Leopold (Belgium)|Order of Leopold]] of the [[Kingdom of Belgium]] \u2013 23 March 1935<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=34145|date=26 March 1935|page=2054|nolink=y}}</ref> (Grand Officer: 26 July 1917<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=30202 |supp=y|date=24 July 1917|page=7590|nolink=y}}</ref>)\n\n===Arms===\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|image = [[File:Coronet of a British Viscount.svg|centre|150px]][[File:Allenby Escutcheon.png|centre|200px]]\n|escutcheon = Per bend Argent and Gules in the sinister three crescents two and one of the second and in the dexter three horses\u2019 heads erased one and two of the first all within a bordure Azure.\n|crest = Issuant out of a crescent Gules a demi-lion Proper.\n|supporters = Dexter a horse reguardant Or sinister a camel reguardant Argent.\n|motto = Fide Et Labore <ref>{{cite book|title=Burke's Peerage |date=1949}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Allenby Bridge]]\n*[[Allenby Gardens, South Australia]]\n*[[Allenby Square]], Jerusalem\n*[[Allenby Street]], Tel Aviv\n*[[Allenby, British Columbia]]\n*[[Allenby, Toronto]]\n*[[Army Manoeuvres of 1912]]\n*[[Mandatory Palestine]]\n*[[Victory Services Club]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=Note}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JdSNAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA146|title=Encyclopedia of the Documentary Film|last=Aitken|first= Ian|publisher=Taylor & Francis Group|year= 2007|isbn=978-1579584450}}\n* {{cite book|title=Allenby|last=Gardner|first=Brian|publisher=London: Cassell|year=