ils/in.ernet.dli.2015.174199|last=Wavell|first=Archibald|publisher=London: Harrap|year= 1943|oclc=68009347}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Edmund Allenby, 1st Viscount Allenby}}\n* [https://www.pbs.org/lawrenceofarabia/players/allenby.html General Allenby], PBS feature on Lawrence of Arabia\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Viscount Wavell}}\n* [http://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/person.php?LinkID=mp00085 Edmund Henry Hynman Allenby, 1st Viscount Allenby (1861\u20131936), Field Marshal: Sitter in 29 portraits] (National Portrait Gallery)\n* [https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1922/03/05/98994758.pdf Lord Allenby&nbsp;\u2013 High Commissioner of Egypt. The New York Times, 5 March 1922 ]\n* [https://blogs.uchicago.edu/oi/1920/06/lord-allenbys-special-train-do.shtml Lord Allenby's Special Train, Dock Siding, Port Said, Egypt]\n* [http://www.criticalpast.com/video/65675050558_Sir-Edmund-Allenby_World-War-I_Jerusalem-proclamation_Jaffa-Gate Historic film footage of General Edmund Allenby entering Jerusalem on foot and reading Jerusalem proclamation, 11 December 1917.]\n*[http://www.nzetc.org/tm/scholarly/tei-WH1-Sina-t1-front-d7.html His introduction to ''The New Zealanders in Sinai nd Palestine'']\n* [http://www.britishpathe.com/video/corps-of-commissionaires/query/uniforms/ British Pathe video of 1926 [[Corps of Commissionaires]] inspection by Viscount Allenby]\n* [http://www.shapell.org/Collection/Historical-Figures/Allenby-Edmund Signed Photo of Edmund Allenby Entering Jerusalem]\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/000379}}\n\n<br>\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-new|reason=British mobilization}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[1st Cavalry Division (United Kingdom)|GOC 1st Cavalry Division]]|years=August &nbsp;\u2013 October 1914}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Beauvoir De Lisle|H. de B. de Lisle]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Herbert Plumer, 1st Viscount Plumer|Herbert Plumer]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[V Corps (United Kingdom)|GOC V Corps]]|years=May 1915&nbsp;\u2013 October 1915}}\n